12. praecinuisset: i.e. she uttered the incantation as she paced about the siclr bed aud Tibullus followed with the sulphur. The word does not neces· arily imply that she acted as a praecantatrix, ae. that Tib. repeated the charm after her. In Ovid, Ars Amat. 2, 329-330 above, she is apparently unaided and, in fact, ipse here (=‘in person’; cp. 1, 1, 7n.) twice repeated emphasizes his special devotion, since this fonction was regularly performed by the saga who was apt to call upon the girl’s lover to furnish the materials.
